body:
Ghost was nerfed because it was just really good on escaping ganks or chasing down people, it was becoming a requirement in higher elos and major play.

. . .

So why can&#039;t Ghost be good but Flash is still taken on literally 95% of the champion roster? How does flash escape this death trap? Ghost benefited melee more than ranged too, it was an exceptional ability for {{champion:266}}  {{champion:48}} {{champion:41}} {{champion:24}} {{champion:23}} 

If ghost was used - that&#039;s a summoner spell that was lost in order to survive a gank, right? So why basically &#039;remove&#039; ghost in play when people will literally maul you in chat for not taking flash. Well, I mean, unless you&#039;re playing {{champion:35}} 

IMO - It is because if Flash was nerfed, melee would be pretty much nonexistent - even worse than ranged VS melee as it is - but right now, ranged is already dominating - so I can understand why flash isn&#039;t nerfed or just removed . . . but I don&#039;t understand why nerfing ghost . . .

Thoughts?
